07/11/2004
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia -- The South Eastern Europe Brigade (SEEBRIG) should be ready for its first mission by mid-2005, according to a decision at the annual meeting of the Southeast Europe Defence Ministerial (SEDM) process held in Ljubljana on Friday (5 November).
No specific task has been scheduled for the time being, but SEDM participants plan to initiate talks with NATO, the EU and the UN, according to Bulgarian Defence Minister Nikolay Svinarov.
Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serbia-Montenegro attended the conference for the first time as observers.
(Sega, Utrinski Vesnik - 06/11/04;
Mediapool, Tanjug - 05/11/04)
